			"editorData": {
				"HowToTrigger": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "To trigger ROTHE ARE AFRAID, NOT MET\r\n1. Start the game.\r\n2. Use Recon command: \"loadlevel WLD_Main_A\"\r\n3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.\r\n4. Talk with Morgya.\r\n\r\nTo trigger ROTHE ARE AFRAID, MET\r\n1. Start the game.\r\n2. Use Recon command: \"loadlevel WLD_Main_A\"\r\n3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.\r\n4. Talk with Morgya.\r\n5. Talk to Morgya again.\r\n\r\nTo trigger ROTHE ARE DEAD\r\n1. Start the game.\r\n2. Use Recon command: \"loadlevel WLD_Main_A\"\r\n3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.\r\n4. Use Recon command: \"SetGlobalOsirisFlag UND_FearfulRothe_State_RotheAreDead\"\r\n5. Talk with Morgya.\r\n\r\nTo trigger ROTHE CALM, RUBBLE STILL THERE\r\n1. Start the game.\r\n2. Use Recon command: \"loadlevel WLD_Main_A\"\r\n3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster\r\n4. Use Recon command: \"addDebugSpell Shout_SpeakWithAnimals\" and \"infiniteAp\"\r\n5. Talk with the Rothe in front of the herdmaster and convince it to attack the rubble.\r\n6. Rapidly talk with Morgya while rubbles are still up.\r\n\r\nTo trigger ROTHE CALM, RUBBLE REMOVED\r\n..."
				},
